transliteration: Ik Oankaar Waaheguroo Joo Koo Fateh||
translation: The Lord is one and the Victory is of the Lord.

gurmukhi: mih`K deIq sUrXM ] biFE su loh pUrXM ]
transliteration: Mahikkh Daoot Soorayan|| Badhio Su Loh Poorayan||

gurmukhi: su dyv rwj jIqXM ] qiRlok rwj kIqXM ]1]
transliteration: Su Dev Raaj Jeetayan|| Trilok Raaj Kootayan||1||
translation: He conuered Indra, the king of gods; and ruled over the three worlds.1.

gurmukhi: Bjy su dyvqw qbY ] iek`qR hoie kY sbY ]
transliteration: Bhaje Su Devtaa Tabai|| Ikattra Hoe Kai Sabai||
translation: At that time the gods ran away; and all of them gathered together.

gurmukhi: mhysrw clM bsy ] ibsyK ic`q mo qRsy ]2]
transliteration: Mahesaraa Chalan Base|| Bisekh Chitt Mo Trase||2||
translation: They inhabited the Kailash mountain; with great fear in their mind.2.

gurmukhi: jugys Bys Dwr kY ] Bjy hiQAwr fwr kY ]
transliteration: Jouges Bhes Dhaar Kai|| Bhaje Hathiaar Daar Kai||
translation: They disguised themselves as great Yogis; and throwing their weapons, they all ran away.

gurmukhi: pukwr AwrqM cly ] ibsUr sUrmw Bly ]3]
transliteration: Poukaar Aaratan Chale|| Bisoor Soormaa Bhale||3||
translation: Crying in great distress they walked. The fine heroes were in great agony.3.

gurmukhi: brK ikqy qhw rhy ] su du`K doh mo shy ]
transliteration: Barakh Kite Tahaa Rahe|| Su Doukkh Deh Mo Sahe||
translation: They lived there for may years; and endured many sufferings on their bodies.

gurmukhi: jgqR mwiq iDAwieXM ] su jYq p`qR pwieXM ]4]
transliteration: Jagadra Maat(i) Dhiaaeyan|| Su Jait Pattra Paaeyan||4||
translation: They mediated on the mother of the universe; for conquering the demon Mahishasura.4.

gurmukhi: pRsMn dyvqw Bey ] crMn pUjby Dey ]
transliteration: Prasann Devtaa Bhae|| Charann Poojabe Dhae||
translation: The gods wrere pleased; and sped to worship the feet of the goddess.
They stood before her; and recited her eulogy.5.
